		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's not the full thing (no games included), but this main part of the source shows most of what was involved.  And the .NES file shows it in action. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br /><a href="http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/multmenu.nes" class="postlink">http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/multmenu.nes</a>
<br /><a href="http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/multi.s" class="postlink">http://www.parodius.com/~memblers/nes/multi.s</a>
<br />
<br />This cart didn't even work right on my MMC1 board, turns out it was because it was some specific version of MMC1A that starts in a random bank.

		

